♫ Let's hold hands tightly and match our footsteps ♫

2
00:00:27,910 --> 00:00:30,480
[Adapted from Joo Young Hyun's webtoon, "I Don't Want to Do Anything."]

3
00:00:34,730 --> 00:00:39,970
[Summer Strike]

4
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:53,750
[Lee Yeo Reum]
[Summer Strike: Episode 2]

5
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:20,700
[Angok Public Library]

6
00:03:17,590 --> 00:03:21,930
[800 Literature]

7
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,070
[The Old Man and the Sea]

8
00:03:49,526 --> 00:03:53,146
"A man is not made for defeat."

9
00:03:53,945 --> 00:03:58,815
"A person can be destroyed, but not defeated."

10
00:04:03,653 --> 00:04:07,263
All right, let's settle down in this town.

11
00:04:17,324 --> 00:04:19,084
Excuse me.

12
00:04:28,390 --> 00:04:30,320
Excuse me, Unnie.

13
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:37,292
Where can I find the real estate agency around here?

14
00:04:45,801 --> 00:04:47,951
I'm sorry.

15
00:04:48,859 --> 00:04:50,859
I'm so sorry.

16
00:04:58,267 --> 00:05:01,285
[Angok Public Library]

17
00:05:01,285 --> 00:05:03,920
Hey, it's my ball!

18
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:06,050
Hey, pass the ball to me!

19
00:05:06,830 --> 00:05:07,870
Pass it!

20
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:09,427
Hey, you over there!

21
00:05:09,427 --> 00:05:11,522
Hey, Old Lady, with the backpack! Pass the ball here!

22
00:05:11,522 --> 00:05:13,397
The ball! Pass it to us!

23
00:05:13,397 --> 00:05:15,832
- Me?
- You are the only one there!

24
00:05:15,832 --> 00:05:18,802
Kick the ball this way!

25
00:05:18,802 --> 00:05:23,372
Hey, Boys! I'm not an old lady!

26
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:36,054
- Oh, no!
- Dae Beom!

27
00:05:36,054 --> 00:05:39,329
- Get up!
- Is your head okay?

28
00:05:39,329 --> 00:05:41,967
- Breathe!
- Are you okay?

29
00:05:41,967 --> 00:05:44,482
I'm so sorry.

30
00:05:44,482 --> 00:05:47,837
How dare you do that to him!

31
00:05:47,837 --> 00:05:49,587
What is this?

32
00:05:49,587 --> 00:05:51,660
Get out of here!

33
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:55,650
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry!

34
00:06:05,282 --> 00:06:07,232
It's a hand-drawn map.

35
00:06:15,626 --> 00:06:17,890
I said it was fine.

36
00:06:17,890 --> 00:06:20,830
When you see those punks again, give my name to them.

37
00:06:20,830 --> 00:06:22,966
Bae Seong Min, the bronze medal from the Junior Athletic Game.

38
00:06:22,966 --> 00:06:24,176
I'm leaving now.

39
00:06:24,176 --> 00:06:27,191
- Wait!
- Hey, hey!

40
00:06:27,191 --> 00:06:29,726
- Boss!
- Wait, hold on.

41
00:06:29,726 --> 00:06:32,120
Hey, wait. Hold on.

42
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:33,185
Oh, my back.

43
00:06:33,185 --> 00:06:36,730
- Boss, get off my leg!
- Wait, wait.

44
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,590
Hold on for a second.

45
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:43,102
Do you have strong glue?

46
00:06:43,102 --> 00:06:46,365
Go check by the brushes, over there.

47
00:06:46,365 --> 00:06:47,908
Are you okay?

48
00:06:47,908 --> 00:06:50,023
You should have been more careful.

49
00:06:50,023 --> 00:06:52,058
It's crazy!

50
00:06:52,058 --> 00:06:55,988
Wow, it will hurt in a while!

51
00:06:57,316 --> 00:07:01,626
I went too far.

52
00:07:17,646 --> 00:07:20,356
- Excuse me.
- What is it?

53
00:07:21,489 --> 00:07:23,234
The glue is 2,000 won.

54
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:25,704
It's not about that.

55
00:07:25,704 --> 00:07:27,600
Bom, where are you going?

56
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,767
All the stuff here is lame so I'm leaving.

57
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:33,036
Why did that brat come here when she didn't buy anything?

58
00:07:33,036 --> 00:07:35,247
Miss, I told you. It's 2,000 won.

59
00:07:35,247 --> 00:07:37,400
Oh, right.

60
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:39,573
Are you okay?

61
00:07:39,573 --> 00:07:42,353
- Here.
- All right.

62
00:07:42,353 --> 00:07:44,848
Take care.

63
00:07:44,848 --> 00:07:47,238
Have a nice day.

64
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:52,560
I caught you.

65
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,460
Come over here.

66
00:08:06,737 --> 00:08:09,031
Go play somewhere else!

67
00:08:09,031 --> 00:08:11,886
I'll get you if you hit my car with the ball!

68
00:08:11,886 --> 00:08:13,796
Go somewhere else now!

69
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:23,610
There's nobody in the library right now, right?

70
00:08:36,210 --> 00:08:39,228
I don't know how long I have to be stuck in Angok.

71
00:08:39,228 --> 00:08:42,856
Why aren't they transferring me somewhere else?

72
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:45,234
Dae Beom, I failed again.

73
00:08:45,234 --> 00:08:48,044
I can't go into County Office again.

74
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:54,000
It's so annoying. Why is this happening to me?

75
00:08:55,269 --> 00:08:58,460
I want to go to Seoul!

76
00:08:58,460 --> 00:09:01,480
I hate Angok!

77
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,530
I don't know.

78
00:09:10,530 --> 00:09:12,880
I'm sick of all this.

79
00:09:12,886 --> 00:09:15,400
I bought only the glue.

80
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:19,170
I'll know when I see if you bought only the glue or not.

81
00:09:19,170 --> 00:09:23,460
What's this? Why are you carrying around a blanket?

82
00:09:23,460 --> 00:09:25,941
Are you on a backpacking trip?

83
00:09:25,941 --> 00:09:27,631
What's this?

84
00:09:31,363 --> 00:09:33,550
What about this one?

85
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:35,440
- Seong Min.
- Yes?

86
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,980
Check her pockets.

87
00:09:39,371 --> 00:09:43,260
That's right. Miss, can I check your pockets?

88
00:09:43,260 --> 00:09:45,995
- Can I see your pocket?
- What are you doing?

89
00:09:45,995 --> 00:09:48,225
Let me see inside your pocket.

90
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:52,880
I have nothing in here.

91
00:09:55,909 --> 00:09:57,560
It's strange.

92
00:09:57,560 --> 00:10:00,690
That security system was very expensive.

93
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:06,070
What's this?

94
00:10:08,469 --> 00:10:10,670
Are you kidding me?

95
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:12,730
Why are you sticking this around here with you?

96
00:10:12,730 --> 00:10:16,266
I didn't put it there.

97
00:10:16,266 --> 00:10:18,761
What, 4B pencils?

98
00:10:18,761 --> 00:10:20,881
Was there any 4B pencil in her stuff?

99
00:10:21,832 --> 00:10:25,442
Why do you get suspicious of your customer?

100
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,775
Young people these days have brilliant ideas,

101
00:10:34,775 --> 00:10:39,172
and they fix up places like this and live well.

102
00:10:39,172 --> 00:10:41,817
The grandma who owns this place... Oh, be careful.

103
00:10:41,817 --> 00:10:43,669
Does this place have electricity?

104
00:10:43,669 --> 00:10:46,489
Well... Goodness, what was that?

105
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:51,801
How much is the monthly rent here?

106
00:10:51,801 --> 00:10:55,446
It's 500,000 won ($377), but I can ask the owner to lower it a bit.

107
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:57,756
The security deposit is 20 million won ($15,000).

108
00:11:00,702 --> 00:11:04,498
This place asks for a security deposit of 2 million won ($1,500) and a monthly rent of 200,000 won ($150).

109
00:11:04,498 --> 00:11:07,168
But I can cut the rent to 170,000 ($125).

110
00:11:07,168 --> 00:11:08,153
Okay.

111
00:11:08,153 --> 00:11:10,318
But you said the bathroom is outside, right?

112
00:11:10,318 --> 00:11:13,278
Yes, the bathroom is down here, and it's communal.

113
00:11:14,091 --> 00:11:17,981
Where is he scratching? He's even sniffing it.

114
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:21,090
I'm sorry, Young Lady.

115
00:11:21,090 --> 00:11:23,340
I can't let you live here.

116
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:25,780
[Angok Real Estate]

117
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:33,010
It's too bad.

118
00:11:38,039 --> 00:11:40,317
Wait, Young Lady.

119
00:11:40,317 --> 00:11:43,342
This is my wife's idea.

120
00:11:43,342 --> 00:11:45,663
I have one more place to show you.

121
00:11:45,663 --> 00:11:47,029
Where is that?

122
00:11:47,029 --> 00:11:50,989
It's hard to describe in words. Let's go and take a look.

123
00:11:56,356 --> 00:11:58,536
It's this building.

124
00:11:59,428 --> 00:12:01,800
- This isn't a residential building.
- What?

125
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,720
Well, right.

126
00:12:04,683 --> 00:12:07,003
It's not even locked.

127
00:12:08,770 --> 00:12:11,580
- Why don't we go inside and take a look?
- Okay.

128
00:12:11,580 --> 00:12:13,880
Okay, come this way.

129
00:12:18,572 --> 00:12:20,210
What is this?

130
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:22,540
Please, come inside.

131
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:28,088
This was the biggest billiard in town a while ago.

132
00:12:28,088 --> 00:12:30,180
Wow, look at the open space!

133
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:33,170
You can play soccer in here.

134
00:12:33,986 --> 00:12:37,731
When they were building this, they poured a lot of cement.

135
00:12:37,731 --> 00:12:42,081
So the building is very sturdy! It'll never collapse.

136
00:12:42,971 --> 00:12:46,642
Right, the rooftop! You can go up to the rooftop when the weather is nice.

137
00:12:46,642 --> 00:12:51,872
It's very sunny up there so the laundry will dry quickly.

138
00:12:53,732 --> 00:12:55,872
That's not all.

139
00:12:56,860 --> 00:13:01,750
You can have the entire building all to yourself.

140
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:05,250
This entire building?

141
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:07,630
That's what I'm saying.

142
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:11,520
So does no one live here?

143
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:15,090
Well, technically, that's what it is.

144
00:13:15,812 --> 00:13:19,432
I guess it's not suitable for a young lady to live alone.

145
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:26,966
How much is the monthly rent?

146
00:13:26,966 --> 00:13:29,351
"The rent"? Do you like this place?

147
00:13:29,351 --> 00:13:31,816
Aigoo, my wife was right!

148
00:13:31,816 --> 00:13:34,051
I knew you would be different.

149
00:13:34,051 --> 00:13:39,140
If that's the case, I'll go right now and settle the rent with the owner.

150
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:42,428
So please hang around here for a bit. Okay?

151
00:13:42,428 --> 00:13:44,368
Wait, Sir?

152
00:13:49,997 --> 00:13:52,450
Boss, it's me.

153
00:13:52,450 --> 00:13:54,880
How are you?

154
00:13:55,586 --> 00:13:59,281
I have something to discuss with you.

155
00:13:59,281 --> 00:14:02,910
Why did you get all this stuff?

156
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:07,810
- Okay, what is it?
- Boss.

157
00:14:07,810 --> 00:14:12,930
Today, I showed houses to a young lady who came from Seoul.

158
00:14:12,930 --> 00:14:17,223
And suddenly, I thought of you.

159
00:14:17,223 --> 00:14:19,326
Why did you think of me?

160
00:14:22,571 --> 00:14:25,170
What if I show her that place?

161
00:14:25,170 --> 00:14:26,690
What place?

162
00:14:26,690 --> 00:14:29,880
The first floor is not suitable, but the billiard room on the second floor might be nice.

163
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:33,332
No, we already decided to sell that to Chang Soo.

164
00:14:33,332 --> 00:14:37,363
Also, how can a person live there?

165
00:14:37,363 --> 00:14:41,281
But is she a nice person?

166
00:14:41,281 --> 00:14:44,632
Yes, she looks like a very sincere person.

167
00:14:44,632 --> 00:14:49,542
But what if she hears about the rumor later?

168
00:16:08,594 --> 00:16:11,263
Those areas like Yang Yang boomed since young people moved there!

169
00:16:11,263 --> 00:16:15,846
You know how much their rentals and land prices rose.

170
00:16:15,846 --> 00:16:19,361
Hey, Brat! Where the heck did you go? You were supposed to look after the store.

171
00:16:19,361 --> 00:16:22,380
I just went to Hyung Chang Soo's place for a minute.

172
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:24,650
What brings you here, Sir?

173
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:28,989
I just had to talk to your father about something.

174
00:16:28,989 --> 00:16:34,114
Seong Min, I don't think we can sell that building to Chang Soo.

175
00:16:34,114 --> 00:16:37,649
My goodness! Father!

176
00:16:37,649 --> 00:16:40,034
Are you out of your mind?

177
00:16:40,034 --> 00:16:43,209
I'm on my way back from persuading Hyung Chang Soo.

178
00:16:43,209 --> 00:16:46,281
He'll sign the contract this week and already prepared the deposit.

179
00:16:46,281 --> 00:16:48,008
That's right, the contract!

180
00:16:48,008 --> 00:16:52,013
We haven't signed the contract yet! So if the owner changes his mind, then it won't happen.

181
00:16:52,013 --> 00:16:54,573
He's right. You need a signed contract to have legal effect.

182
00:16:54,573 --> 00:16:56,100
Please stay out of this, Ahjussi!

183
00:16:56,100 --> 00:17:02,570
After listening to Mr. Kwak, I realized it would be a huge loss if I sold it at that price.

184
00:17:02,570 --> 00:17:06,652
Father, do you remember how long that building has been empty?

185
00:17:06,652 --> 00:17:10,197
Why don't you go over there with Mr. Kwak right now?

186
00:17:10,197 --> 00:17:14,250
- Go where?
- Go to the billiards and sign the contract.

187
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:17,930
I heard a good fridge came out in the town market so I must get it.

188
00:17:17,930 --> 00:17:19,481
Have a good night, Boss!
[Economy Store]

189
00:17:19,481 --> 00:17:23,011
Wait, Father! What contract?

190
00:17:28,757 --> 00:17:31,000
- Who is it?
- My goodness!

191
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,290
- What's going on? Who's there?
- Mr. Kwak?

192
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:35,250
Honey, what's going on?

193
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:38,200
- Look over there!
- What?

194
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,903
My goodness! W-Who are you?

195
00:17:40,903 --> 00:17:44,278
I'm here to see the room to rent. Who are you?

196
00:17:44,278 --> 00:17:46,733
- What?
- What? Are you here to see the room?

197
00:17:46,733 --> 00:17:48,595
Hyung! Hyung Chang Soo!

198
00:17:48,595 --> 00:17:51,140
Seriously!

199
00:17:51,140 --> 00:17:57,590
Hey! How can you get a tenant when you said we could come in and measure the space?

200
00:17:57,590 --> 00:18:01,160
No, it's not like that. I also just found out about this.

201
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:02,810
Let's talk outside. Shall we?

202
00:18:02,810 --> 00:18:04,490
Talk about what? Just say it right here!

203
00:18:04,490 --> 00:18:06,280
Chang Soo, there's a customer here so...

204
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:08,210
- What? A customer?
- Sister!

205
00:18:08,210 --> 00:18:10,630
There's nothing to worry about! Let's go outside.

206
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:14,110
- Let's go outside first and talk.
- Hey! Seriously, you!

207
00:18:14,110 --> 00:18:16,310
No, I'm also surprised!

208
00:18:16,310 --> 00:18:19,100
What the heck is this?

209
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,445
Are you okay?

210
00:18:21,445 --> 00:18:23,600
I bet you are startled.

211
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:27,730
Why don't we go to the brightest spot since there's no lighting here?

212
00:18:27,730 --> 00:18:29,830
Why is she screaming so much?

213
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:32,196
Stop pushing me!

214
00:18:32,196 --> 00:18:35,895
- Well, you aren't walking out.
- Stop pushing me! I'll walk on my own.

215
00:18:35,895 --> 00:18:38,050
Hey, who's that woman?

216
00:18:38,050 --> 00:18:40,604
What do you mean by a customer? Why?

217
00:18:40,604 --> 00:18:44,370
Is your father selling the building to that woman for a few more bucks?

218
00:18:44,370 --> 00:18:47,250
Listen, that woman is here to see the space to rent.

219
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:49,620
Do you think it makes sense? That's why I'm saying don't worry!

220
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:53,800
But why did you put the space for rent without our permission?

221
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:56,120
Do you think that makes any sense?

222
00:18:56,120 --> 00:18:59,510
I never put the room for rent. And I'm not planning to do so!

223
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:03,715
My father did all this! So I'm saying...

224
00:19:03,715 --> 00:19:05,690
Why are they shouting so much?

225
00:19:05,690 --> 00:19:07,631
I'll ask my father to take responsibility.

226
00:19:07,631 --> 00:19:10,240
Sir, why don't you two go to your store?

227
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:13,450
I'll take care of everything here and come to you later.

228
00:19:13,450 --> 00:19:16,290
Seong Min, get yourself together, okay?

229
00:19:16,290 --> 00:19:19,080
Yes, I'm Bae Seong Min! I'll solve it all.

230
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:21,130
- Stop kidding me.
- Let's go.

231
00:19:21,130 --> 00:19:24,000
I'll see you later.

232
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,110
Please, stop it!

233
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:31,470
Did I do something wrong?

234
00:19:31,470 --> 00:19:33,920
No, no, not at all!

235
00:19:33,920 --> 00:19:37,961
I think there was some misunderstanding, but you don't have to worry about it.

236
00:19:37,961 --> 00:19:39,250
Please don't worry about it.

237
00:19:39,250 --> 00:19:42,891
Ahjussi! Ahjussi!

238
00:19:42,891 --> 00:19:46,840
Ahjussi, what kind of tricks did you pull on my father again?

239
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:50,020
Oh, please! A customer is here.

240
00:19:50,020 --> 00:19:52,890
This is the son of the building's owner.

241
00:19:52,890 --> 00:19:55,640
- Wait!
- Weren't you at the Economy Store?

242
00:19:55,640 --> 00:20:01,534
Miss, I was an athlete. So I hate talking for a long time.

243
00:20:01,534 --> 00:20:06,482
You say you are moving here, but do you even know what kind of place this is?

244
00:20:06,482 --> 00:20:08,692
This building has been empty for twenty years.

245
00:20:08,692 --> 00:20:10,419
Why do you think that is?

246
00:20:10,419 --> 00:20:12,639
"For twenty years"?

247
00:20:13,255 --> 00:20:17,009
Will you really act like this? It's all settled with your father already.

248
00:20:17,009 --> 00:20:19,830
- You said she's going to rent the room!
- What's going on?

249
00:20:19,830 --> 00:20:21,709
It's of no concern.

250
00:20:21,709 --> 00:20:24,109
What do you mean, of no concern?

251
00:20:24,109 --> 00:20:27,040
- A person died in here before.
- What?

252
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:29,463
Can you live in a place where someone died? I could never do that!

253
00:20:29,463 --> 00:20:31,507
Seong Min, are you really doing this?

254
00:20:31,507 --> 00:20:35,162
Well, it's completely up to you.

255
00:20:35,162 --> 00:20:37,667
But after that one incident, nothing has happened.

256
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:39,702
Ahjussi.

257
00:20:39,702 --> 00:20:43,397
Look at her face. She's totally freaked out.

258
00:20:43,397 --> 00:20:45,910
Let's not do this in the dark.

259
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:48,330
Let's go out to talk. A ghost will come!

260
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:51,920
Seriously! If you keep acting like this, I'll tell your father!

261
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:53,740
Go ahead, tell him! Tell him!

262
00:20:53,740 --> 00:20:56,400
And also, honestly, you are acting weird.

263
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:59,640
Why do you show this space when many great places are available?

264
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:01,930
- Are you scamming or something?
- Young Lady!

265
00:21:01,930 --> 00:21:03,850
It's 50,000 won.

266
00:21:03,850 --> 00:21:05,370
- Excuse me?
- What?

267
00:21:05,370 --> 00:21:08,090
The monthly rent of this space is 50,000 won ($38)!

268
00:21:08,090 --> 00:21:10,200
- What did you just say?
- ₩50,000?

269
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,280
Why would I show you this space if it didn't have that advantage?

270
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:16,170
Wait, do you think that price makes sense right now?

271
00:21:16,170 --> 00:21:19,560
I settled the rent to be 50,000 won with the owner

272
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:23,420
on the condition that you manage this building.

273
00:21:23,420 --> 00:21:25,850
Are you saying Father will rent this for ₩50,000 won a month?

274
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:27,600
Yes!

275
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:30,550
Okay, I'll call my dad to check. Agasshi (Miss), get prepared!

276
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:32,250
It's 50,000 won.

277
00:21:32,250 --> 00:21:34,830
If it's for 12 months,

278
00:21:34,830 --> 00:21:37,470
it's 600,000 won ($450).

279
00:21:37,470 --> 00:21:40,360
What do you say?

280
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:44,870
Then... I'll rent this place.

281
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:45,990
What?

282
00:21:45,990 --> 00:21:48,020
You made a great choice!

283
00:21:48,020 --> 00:21:49,900
Hello? Father!

284
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:52,180
I'll pray for your blessings.

285
00:21:52,180 --> 00:21:55,770
Our Father in Heaven, this sister will start a new life in this place.

286
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:57,810
What? But, Dad!

287
00:21:57,810 --> 00:22:01,340
- Please look after her with all your might. Amen.
- Wait, Dad!

288
00:22:01,340 --> 00:22:03,270
This is driving me crazy!

289
00:22:03,270 --> 00:22:06,300
Seong Min! Let's go.

290
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:08,340
Wait, please!

291
00:22:08,340 --> 00:22:10,822
Did you see the bathroom here?

292
00:22:10,822 --> 00:22:14,183
Even if you poop, it doesn't flush! You can't take a shower here!

293
00:22:14,183 --> 00:22:18,380
How are you going to live in this rough space? Please reconsider this!

294
00:22:18,380 --> 00:22:21,820
[Lee Yeo Reum]

295
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,980
I'm glad you liked the space.

296
00:22:24,980 --> 00:22:26,370
Thank you.

297
00:22:26,370 --> 00:22:29,980
- Ahjumma.
- Okay, then you can send 600,000 won for yearly rent.

298
00:22:29,980 --> 00:22:31,890
Okay.

299
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,470
I just sent the money to you.

300
00:22:36,470 --> 00:22:38,180
Why don't you check it?

301
00:22:40,990 --> 00:22:42,820
How much is your commission?

302
00:22:42,820 --> 00:22:45,810
No, you don't pay for me showing the place.

303
00:22:45,810 --> 00:22:47,990
All we need is for you to live there well.

304
00:22:47,990 --> 00:22:50,360
Thank you so much.

305
00:22:52,160 --> 00:22:57,320
Can I move in there tonight?

306
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:59,490
Oh, from tonight?

307
00:22:59,490 --> 00:23:01,680
That place doesn't have electricity or anything.

308
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:03,880
I'm fine with it.

309
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:06,660
Well, the contract starts today.

310
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:09,330
I can't believe you are really doing this.

311
00:23:10,930 --> 00:23:13,000
Seong Min.

312
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,230
You have to hand her the keys.

313
00:23:19,730 --> 00:23:21,770
Here you go.

314
00:23:21,770 --> 00:23:24,530
Honey, can you bring that thing I asked for earlier?

315
00:23:24,530 --> 00:23:26,180
Right, okay.

316
00:23:26,180 --> 00:23:27,400
[Angok Real Estate]

317
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,760
It's for you since that space has no electricity right now.

318
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:31,050
Thank you so much.

319
00:23:31,050 --> 00:23:33,430
I hope you have a nice life there.

320
00:23:33,430 --> 00:23:34,740
Oh, that guy.

321
00:23:34,740 --> 00:23:37,220
- Thank you for everything.
- Have a good night!

322
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:39,240
Take care.

323
00:23:43,210 --> 00:23:44,800
Excuse me.

324
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:50,350
Thank you for telling me that story first.

325
00:23:51,370 --> 00:23:54,920
If I had heard it later, it would have been scarier.

326
00:23:56,650 --> 00:23:58,030
Whatever.

327
00:23:58,030 --> 00:24:01,980
If something breaks down, you fix it on your own.

328
00:24:01,980 --> 00:24:07,020
If you can't live there anymore, move out anytime. Okay?

329
00:24:07,020 --> 00:24:08,560
Yes.

330
00:24:21,440 --> 00:24:23,840
I got a place to live.

331
00:25:16,850 --> 00:25:20,710
After quitting my job,

332
00:25:20,710 --> 00:25:24,650
I lay in bed for two whole days.

333
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:27,488
I was afraid.

334
00:25:28,170 --> 00:25:33,320
I didn't know what to do at all.

335
00:25:38,580 --> 00:25:42,420
So first, I decided to leave Seoul.

336
00:25:42,420 --> 00:25:46,800
Because this city is overwhelming for a jobless person like me.

337
00:26:00,545 --> 00:26:05,960
I threw out my ex-boyfriend's stuff that I couldn't touch until then.

338
00:26:09,580 --> 00:26:16,600
And I decided to keep only things that fit in one backpack.

339
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:22,610
When I started organizing stuff, I realized how much I had bought.

340
00:26:22,610 --> 00:26:25,990
I thoughtlessly bought mugs that were pretty,

341
00:26:25,990 --> 00:26:29,810
plus dishes I used only once for the housewarming party.

342
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:36,840
Clothes I didn't even know existed after buying them,

343
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:40,950
and cheap shoes I kept buying as habit from shop stalls,

344
00:26:41,900 --> 00:26:46,640
I picked one of each category that I absolutely needed.

345
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:50,840
The competition was fiercer than a big company's interview.

346
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:56,090
Things I didn't need were instantly sold when I put them in the online market.

347
00:27:01,090 --> 00:27:03,070
Goodbye.

348
00:27:03,070 --> 00:27:05,950
Goodbye to my six-pyeong (215 sq ft) life.

349
00:27:13,550 --> 00:27:16,620
Before this journey is over,

350
00:27:16,620 --> 00:27:19,100
I hope I can find the answer.

351
00:27:20,510 --> 00:27:25,080
I want to figure out how to live my life from now on.

352
00:27:59,130 --> 00:28:01,880
This place has a great sky view.

353
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:19,960
Hello.

354
00:28:21,670 --> 00:28:23,890
Hello.

355
00:28:25,380 --> 00:28:26,930
How can I help you?

356
00:28:26,930 --> 00:28:31,940
I would like a membership card for this library.

357
00:28:31,940 --> 00:28:34,720
But you need a local address to get one.

358
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:36,120
Yes, I do have one.

359
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:38,950
- Did you move here?
- Yes.

360
00:28:38,950 --> 00:28:40,970
We'll help you with that over here.

361
00:28:51,660 --> 00:28:53,470
Well...

362
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:57,550
Are you okay after what happened yesterday?

363
00:29:01,158 --> 00:29:03,238
I'm sorry about that.

364
00:29:04,630 --> 00:29:08,560
Also, thank you for the map that you drew for me.

365
00:29:12,403 --> 00:29:14,090
What is it about?

366
00:29:14,090 --> 00:29:16,500
What map?

367
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:28,750
Here it is.

368
00:29:30,711 --> 00:29:33,056
Isn't this address the billiards?

369
00:29:34,064 --> 00:29:36,793
Are you living there?

370
00:29:36,793 --> 00:29:38,413
- Yes.
- Oh.

371
00:29:44,040 --> 00:29:46,670
Thank you.

372
00:29:48,380 --> 00:29:50,460
[Library Membership Card of Angok Library]
[Name: Lee Yeo Reum]

373
00:29:54,610 --> 00:29:57,710
How can anybody live there?

374
00:30:01,530 --> 00:30:03,420
Hello.

375
00:30:37,230 --> 00:30:38,610
Excuse me.

376
00:30:38,610 --> 00:30:40,390
Your bag is over there.

377
00:30:40,390 --> 00:30:42,950
It's not about that.

378
00:30:45,690 --> 00:30:48,030
Excuse me, Lady. This is my seat.

379
00:30:48,030 --> 00:30:50,300
So don't sit here from now on.

380
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:53,800
Kim Bom! Keep it down.

381
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:56,610
Why is she always picking on me?

382
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:08,860
Wait!

383
00:31:23,810 --> 00:31:25,530
Hello?

384
00:31:25,530 --> 00:31:29,180
Can you come out to the front of the library for a second?

385
00:31:29,180 --> 00:31:30,440
Who's this?

386
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:32,320
You'll know when you come downstairs.

387
00:31:32,320 --> 00:31:35,300
Who are you to say come out or not?

388
00:31:35,300 --> 00:31:37,430
Hello?

389
00:31:37,430 --> 00:31:38,990
Hey, Kim Bom.

390
00:31:38,990 --> 00:31:41,940
What the heck are you doing? Take your phone call outside.

391
00:31:58,830 --> 00:31:59,940
What is it?

392
00:31:59,940 --> 00:32:03,240
I think our phones got mixed up.

393
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:05,500
What?

394
00:32:05,500 --> 00:32:07,320
Take a look.

395
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:10,540
Wait!

396
00:32:10,540 --> 00:32:13,950
I think it's confusing as we don't have phone cases.

397
00:32:16,300 --> 00:32:18,430
Is it your grandma?

398
00:32:18,430 --> 00:32:19,950
Me?

399
00:32:19,950 --> 00:32:23,250
You can tell I'm a high-school student by looking at me.

400
00:32:23,250 --> 00:32:26,410
No, I meant your phone's wallpaper.

401
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:31,300
Why take someone else's phone without permission and look at stuff?

402
00:32:31,300 --> 00:32:34,490
- I'm sorry.
- Be mindful!

403
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:37,340
Excuse me!

404
00:32:38,980 --> 00:32:40,690
What is it now?

405
00:32:43,190 --> 00:32:45,170
It's nothing.

406
00:32:52,750 --> 00:32:55,220
Let's just have some lunch.

407
00:32:57,620 --> 00:33:00,310
Enjoy!

408
00:33:00,310 --> 00:33:03,840
[Jeil Restaurant]

409
00:33:04,860 --> 00:33:07,570
What can I get for you?

410
00:33:07,570 --> 00:33:10,340
Oh, hello!

411
00:33:10,340 --> 00:33:13,184
What do you want?

412
00:33:13,184 --> 00:33:14,920
Can I have one sundae (blood sausage) soup?

413
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:18,850
- One sundae soup!
- Okay!

414
00:33:18,850 --> 00:33:22,180
- Table number two's food is ready!
- Okay!

415
00:33:25,470 --> 00:33:27,710
Enjoy.

416
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:41,200
Can we have another bottle of soju?

417
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:43,230
Coming!

418
00:33:43,230 --> 00:33:46,430
Is it okay for you to drink this much?

419
00:33:46,430 --> 00:33:48,870
I'll just have another drink.

420
00:33:54,350 --> 00:33:57,540
That's right. I'll live here not worrying what other people think.

421
00:33:57,540 --> 00:33:59,700
I'll do as I wish.

422
00:33:59,700 --> 00:34:01,860
Ma'am!

423
00:34:03,530 --> 00:34:05,940
Ma'am!

424
00:34:05,940 --> 00:34:09,080
Can I have a bottle of soju, please?

425
00:34:25,010 --> 00:34:26,930
It's nice.

426
00:34:26,930 --> 00:34:28,900
Hot and cold.

427
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,640
Who thought of this in the first place?

428
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:16,350
It's the taste of being an adult.

429
00:35:17,890 --> 00:35:20,660
[Jeil Restaurant]

430
00:35:20,660 --> 00:35:24,270
- Thank you for the food! Thanks for food.
- All right.

431
00:35:24,270 --> 00:35:28,120
I'll put it on the tab! See you later!

432
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:30,010
Let's see.

433
00:35:41,120 --> 00:35:44,620
How can someone leave the fishcake dish?

434
00:35:50,450 --> 00:35:52,740
What a disgrace.

435
00:36:02,290 --> 00:36:05,250
[Angok Public Library]

436
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:37,360
Oh, my head hurts.

437
00:36:54,350 --> 00:36:56,890
Why am I here?

438
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:02,050
- Thank you.
- Get home safe.

439
00:37:02,050 --> 00:37:04,780
Thank you for the food!

440
00:37:04,780 --> 00:37:08,070
[10 hours ago]

441
00:37:08,070 --> 00:37:12,070
What's wrong with that young woman to be drunk so early in the day?

442
00:37:13,610 --> 00:37:16,770
[Jeil Restaurant]

443
00:37:17,990 --> 00:37:20,030
Hey, take the ball from him!

444
00:37:27,700 --> 00:37:31,280
- Let's play again.
- Where are you going?

445
00:37:37,130 --> 00:37:39,710
[Angok Public Library]

446
00:38:11,530 --> 00:38:13,250
Is she okay?

447
00:38:13,250 --> 00:38:15,480
Hey, let's hang out in here!

448
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:17,310
If you don't play, you lose! Rock, paper, scissors!

449
00:38:17,310 --> 00:38:19,770
Guys, be quiet!

450
00:38:25,820 --> 00:38:27,770
Is she drunk?

451
00:38:27,770 --> 00:38:31,180
She fainted!

452
00:38:31,180 --> 00:38:33,540
What is this?

453
00:38:33,540 --> 00:38:37,740
Look at her hair! It's funny!

454
00:38:37,740 --> 00:38:40,540
Excuse me! What are you doing right now?

455
00:38:40,540 --> 00:38:44,070
It's not a snake, but the medusa.

456
00:38:44,070 --> 00:38:47,580
- She must be crazy!
- She does look crazy.

457
00:38:47,580 --> 00:38:49,350
Oh, this is the library.

458
00:38:49,350 --> 00:38:51,860
What's wrong with her?

459
00:38:52,930 --> 00:38:55,840
I have to go home.

460
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:58,140
- Open your eyes!
- Boys, get out of the way.

461
00:38:58,140 --> 00:39:01,790
You can't come here after getting drunk.

462
00:39:01,790 --> 00:39:05,140
- I'm sorry.
- Sure!

463
00:39:05,140 --> 00:39:06,190
Press her, press her!

464
00:39:06,190 --> 00:39:09,400
Guys, stop it. Let's all go out now.

465
00:39:10,993 --> 00:39:13,380
Dae Beom, not that way!

466
00:39:13,380 --> 00:39:16,220
Don't take them in there! Dae Beom!

467
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:19,490
I have to go home.

468
00:39:19,490 --> 00:39:22,730
I have to go home...

469
00:39:24,670 --> 00:39:27,040
Wow, I must have lost my mind.

470
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,970
I should go home now.

471
00:39:32,010 --> 00:39:33,960
What is this?

472
00:39:38,128 --> 00:39:41,188
Why did I drink that much?

473
00:39:42,950 --> 00:39:45,020
It's three in the morning!

474
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:54,990
Excuse me!

475
00:39:55,840 --> 00:40:00,080
I'm in here! Is there anyone out there? Please open the door!

476
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:02,240
What do I do?

477
00:40:03,830 --> 00:40:05,800
Right, my phone.

478
00:40:14,730 --> 00:40:17,270
Don't come any closer. Don't come here!

479
00:40:17,270 --> 00:40:21,070
Don't come any closer! Don't come any closer!

480
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:27,190
Mr. Librarian?

481
00:40:34,247 --> 00:40:36,450
Thank you.

482
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:55,680
By the way, why did you stay here until this hour?

483
00:40:57,480 --> 00:40:59,710
Is it because of me?

484
00:41:00,630 --> 00:41:02,610
I'm so sorry.

485
00:41:09,676 --> 00:41:12,230
[I guess now you are awake.]

486
00:41:12,230 --> 00:41:18,630
[The electricity will come back at 8 a.m., and the door will open then.]

487
00:41:18,630 --> 00:41:22,020
So until then, please rest where you feel comfortable.

488
00:41:24,080 --> 00:41:26,930
I guess he can't speak.

489
00:41:27,860 --> 00:41:33,320
But why didn't you wake me up?

490
00:41:36,452 --> 00:41:38,170
Dae Beom, I'll head out first.

491
00:41:38,170 --> 00:41:40,340
Clean up and go, okay?
[7 hours ago]

492
00:41:40,340 --> 00:41:42,410
Bye!

493
00:41:44,420 --> 00:41:46,930
Thank you. See you tomorrow!

494
00:42:57,930 --> 00:43:00,290
You must have tried to wake me.

495
00:43:01,560 --> 00:43:03,710
You should have some sleep.

496
00:43:24,450 --> 00:43:29,800
[If you want to read some books, you can go to the far right by the window.]

497
00:43:29,800 --> 00:43:32,420
That's the brightest spot in here.

498
00:43:34,170 --> 00:43:36,620
Thank you.

499
00:43:53,410 --> 00:43:55,070
This is...

500
00:44:00,300 --> 00:44:02,370
Mr. Librarian?

501
00:44:03,190 --> 00:44:05,150
Mr. Librarian?

502
00:44:10,192 --> 00:44:11,550
Oh, it hurts.

503
00:44:11,550 --> 00:44:13,590
Mr. Librarian!

504
00:44:14,720 --> 00:44:17,610
Wait, Mr. Librarian.

505
00:44:17,610 --> 00:44:20,530
I don't think you have to roll any further.

506
00:44:24,350 --> 00:44:28,050
I just wanted to give this back to you.

507
00:44:31,100 --> 00:44:34,360
That's what I was going to do.

508
00:44:37,190 --> 00:44:42,570
I'll use this until the morning and give it back to you.

509
00:44:46,310 --> 00:44:48,630
Good night.

510
00:44:51,450 --> 00:44:53,220
I'm sorry, but...

511
00:44:54,210 --> 00:44:58,060
Where can I find the restroom?

512
00:45:07,690 --> 00:45:11,490
[The restroom is outside of the doors.]

513
00:45:12,610 --> 00:45:17,900
Why did he give me water to drink when the restroom was outside locked doors?

514
00:45:17,900 --> 00:45:20,780
Now I think of it, he didn't drink and just gave it to me.

515
00:45:20,780 --> 00:45:23,480
No, no. Let's not think about it.

516
00:45:23,480 --> 00:45:26,860
Let's not even think about wanting to go to the bathroom.

517
00:46:02,470 --> 00:46:05,090
It's almost that time.

518
00:46:05,090 --> 00:46:07,550
It's almost 8 o'clock.

519
00:46:08,860 --> 00:46:10,780
Let's hold it in a little more.

520
00:46:15,530 --> 00:46:18,120
Just a bit more...

521
00:46:20,070 --> 00:46:21,920
Please.

522
00:46:33,250 --> 00:46:36,280
I can't let my guard down at the very end.

523
00:46:36,280 --> 00:46:38,440
I shouldn't run.

524
00:46:38,440 --> 00:46:41,480
Nothing can stop this if it starts.

525
00:47:32,470 --> 00:47:34,730
Goodbye.

526
00:47:50,710 --> 00:47:55,550
